post_text: Yankton's Pizza Ranch rocks! Thank you!
shared_text:
Yankton Area Chamber of Commerce
August 7 at 10:36 AM ·

Yankton Pizza Ranch saw a need and got a plan together to help fill the gap. Our Yankton School District had a lunch debt balance of $3,500 and the school district needed some community help to pay off this amount.

The Pizza Ranch team created a fundraiser that, for 2 weeks in May, donated $1 to the Yankton School District Angel Fund for every large pizza sold. In that time, the Yankton Pizza Ranch raised $1,607 and was able to erase almost half of the debt!

Thank you Pizza Ranch for your commitment to our community and school district!

Read More > https://pizzaranch.com/blog/wednesday-story-of-impact-angels-in-action

post_text: Girls who are entering grades 7-12 and are interested in playing high school soccer this fall are encouraged to attend a pre-season meeting Wednesday, July 29 at 6pm in the Yankton College Alumni Hall located on the YHS campus. Any student in grades 9-12 interested in being a student manager should also plan to attend the meeting. Masks will be required. Please limit attendance to players and one parent per player, if possible, to allow for proper social distancing practices. Please use the back parking lot. Contact coach Tyler Schuring with any questions, 605-380-7667. The season is set to start Monday, August 3.

Dear Class of 2020 and Parents/Guardians:

Unfortunately due to the forecast of thunderstorms this afternoon, the graduation ceremony must be moved indoors to the YHS Main Gym. Graduates with the last name Ament-Lange will have a ceremony at noon and Langely-Yaggie will have a ceremony at 2:00 at YHS. Masks are strongly recommended for all in attendance.

The gates will open 30 minutes prior to each ceremony.

As a reminder, each graduate was issued 6 tickets to share. No one will be admitted without a ticket. Due to the limited number of tickets issued, click the link below to watch the live stream of the event(s) at no charge.

https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/events/yankton-high-school-yankton-sd/evtce0b8a8b3d

A photographer will take photos of all of the graduates. More information will be sent regarding how to purchase prints.

Thank you,
Dr. Johnke

The Yankton School Board will hold its regularly scheduled meeting on Monday, July 13 at 5:00 pm. The meeting will be held in the Yankton High School Theatre located at 1801 Summit Street. One of the items on the agenda will be discussion about Yankton School District returning to school for the 2020-2021 school year.

The Yankton School Board will also hold a special school board meeting on Thursday, July 16 at 5:00 pm. On the agenda will be discussion on the return to school for 2020. The meeting will be held in the Yankton High School Theatre located at 1801 Summit Street.

The public is invited to attend both meetings. Social distancing in the theatre and wearing masks are strongly encouraged. To view either meeting via live stream, go to the Yankton School District website, click School Board and then click Live Stream School Board Meeting.

The agenda for both meetings can be found at the following website: www.boarddocs.com/sd/ysd/Board.nsf/Public

post_text:
Want to play Gazelle Soccer? - Coach Tyler Schuring of the reigning State AA Girls Soccer Champions is looking for you!!! All YHS girls 9-12 interested in playing for the Gazelles or becoming a student manager are highly encouraged to reach out to a current Gazelle soccer player or contact Coach Schuring (605-380-7667). We are looking for highly motivated and competitive players. Previous playing experience can be beneficial, but any player willing to learn is encouraged to get involved. After graduating ten quality seniors last year we have plenty of open positions to compete for!!!
- Seventh and eighth graders interested in playing HS soccer should contact Coach Schuring to express your interest and to get information about potentially receiving an invite to play. Participation by seventh and eighth graders will depend on the number of 9-12 participants. - Reach out today and learn about potential summer training options as well as making sure all your paperwork is completed for the school prior to the season!

Yankton School District
April 28 at 8:45 AM ·

A Virtual Graduation will be released on May 17, 2020 at 2:00 pm. The public may view the Virtual Graduation by going to the tab “RECENT NEWS” at the YSD Website and click on the Virtual Graduation tab: https://www.ysd.k12.sd.us/

The victory bell at YHS will ring from 2:00-3:00 on May 17, 2020. On the evening of May 17 the lights will be turned on at Crane-Youngworth Field, Williams Field, YHS Tennis Courts and lighting at Yankton High School to honor our YHS 2020 Graduates.

The Yankton School District is also planning to hold a Graduation Ceremony in the YHS Main Gym on Sunday, July 26, at 1:00 pm, if allowed by recommendations of the CDC as well as state and local health officials.

Information for the Senior Class of 2020:
Class Colors: Red and Black
Class Flower: Iris
Class Motto: “Our Senior Skip Day went a little too far.”
Cap & Gown Color: Black
Tassel Color: Red, White, and Black

A Virtual Graduation will be released on May 17, 2020 at 2:00 pm. The public may view the Virtual Graduation by going to the tab “RECENT NEWS” at the YSD Website and click on the Virtual Graduation tab: https://www.ysd.k12.sd.us/

The victory bell at YHS will ring from 2:00-3:00 on May 17, 2020. On the evening of May 17 the lights will be turned on at Crane-Youngworth Field, Williams Field, YHS Tennis Courts and lighting at Yankton High School to honor our YHS 2020 Graduates.

The Yankton School District is also planning to hold a Graduation Ceremony in the YHS Main Gym on Sunday, July 26, at 1:00 pm, if allowed by recommendations of the CDC as well as state and local health officials.

Information for the Senior Class of 2020:
Class Colors: Red and Black
Class Flower: Iris
Class Motto: “Our Senior Skip Day went a little too far.”
Cap & Gown Color: Black
Tassel Color: Red, White, and Black

post_text:
Dear Parents:

The well-being of our students and families is very important to me. We are all experiencing a very burdensome journey. The purpose of this message is to provide you and your children with some excellent resources during this time. Our School Counselors have done a superb job putting these resources together for you.

Provided below is a link to counseling resources for Elementary, Middle School and High School students. Please take time to look through the resources and make use of these supports. This link will be updated periodically: https://bit.ly/33YfCed

“A little consideration, a little thought for others, makes all the difference.” - Eeyore, Winnie-the-Pooh

You are welcome to reach out to any of us in the Yankton School District. We are here for you.

My best to all of our children!

Dr. Wayne Kindle, Superintendent
Yankton School District
